result.name: Toby Inn

reviews.text: Really cheap place with great authentic chinese food! Loved the pork with black pepper sauce.
Very good value for the great taste. Recommend the Orange Ribs! Surprisingly this is not a tourist trap.

Always good dim sum here - and not costly either. Very much a local restaurant, so don't expect fancy dishes or table linens. No menu - go up to big steam baskets and point out what you want. No English spoken,  just Cantonese. Rinse your dishes with the provided hot water.

A very localized Chinese restaurant, unlike those western style tourist oriented eating places found mostly in Stanley.  Don't expect fancy decoration and attentive service, but you can find old school dim sum here as well as Cantonese dishes.  Price is not costly and they don't have 10% service charge.
Cantonese restaurant, good & tasty steamy Dim Sum.  It’s only one Cantonese tea restaurant and worthy to tasting whenever you are in Stanley.
